    <stitle>HENDRICKSON AIR SUSPENSION WITH TRAILING LEAF SPRINGS - HENDRICKSON AIR SUSPENSION COMPONENTS - PRESSURE
        PROTECTION VALVE
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="1">
        <title>PRESSURE PROTECTION VALVE</title>
        <para>A pressure protection valve located at the vehicle's air storage tanks or on the frame rail protects the
            vehicle's primary air system should a failure occur in the suspension's air system (
            <hotlnk xrefid="f0300706">Figure 6</hotlnk>).
        </para>
        <figure id="f0300706" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g0300706" filename="../figg03/G0300706.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
            <caption>Figure 6. AIR PLUMBING AND COMPONENT DIAGRAM</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1.AIR SUPPLY</callout1>
                <callout1>2.PRESSURE PROTECTION VALVE 90 PSI</callout1>
                <callout1>3.HEIGHT CONTROL LEVELING VALVE</callout1>
                <callout1>4.QUICK RELEASE VALVE</callout1>
                <callout1>5.LEVELING VALVE ARM EXTENSION ROD</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
